@node "Installation" "Installing MBench"
@next "Running"
@prev "Register"
@{b}MBench Installation@{ub}

To install MBench simply run the provided install script.  Full help is
provided on the installer screen.
@endnode


@node "Running" "Running MBench"
@next "Support"
@prev "Installation"
@{b}Running MBench@{ub}

The installation script will automatically cause MBench to be loaded instead
of workbench from the disk it was installed to. MBench can also be run
manually from the CLI with the following format:

Format:
  MBench [PUBSCREEN] [SETTINGS] [PORTNAME] [STARTUP] [CX_PRIORITY] [CX_POPKEY]

Template:
  PUBSCREEN/K,S=SETTINGS/K,P=PORTNAME/K,STARTUP/K,CX_PRIORITY/N/K,CX_POPKEY/K

Specification:

All the additional parameters to MBench are optional.  The meaning of each
of these parameters is as follows.

PUBSCREEN=<Screen> where screen is the name of the public screen to open on.
                   If this screen can't be found, MBench will open on the 
                   default screen.
SETTINGS=<Filename>where filename is the name of a configuration file
                   for MBench to use.
PORTNAME=<Name>    where name is the required name for MBench's Arrex port.
STARTUP=<Filename> where filename is an Arrex script to execute on startup.
CX_PRIORITY=<Priority> where priority is the commodities priority to run 
                       MBench at.
CX_POPKEY=<Description> where description is the key press template to bring
                        MBench to the front.

Example:
  MBench PUBSCREEN=MainScreen SETTINGS=MBench.config
@endnode


