@node "ScrollWindowBottom" "Scroll Window Bottom"
@next "SnapshotWindow"
@prev "SelectPreviousWindow"
@{b}ScrollWindowBottom@{ub}

The ScrollWindowBottom command is used to move the windows display down to
the bottom of the display.

Format:
  ScrollWindowBottom
  [WINDOW] 

Template:
  W=WINDOW/F

Specification: 
WINDOW=<Window>    Where Window is a file name specifying the name of the
                   windows display to move to the bottom of.  If not
                   specified this will move the current windows down to the 
                   bottom of the display.

Callable via:
  ARexx, internally

Example:
  ScrollWindowBottom
  ScrollWindowBottom SYS:Prefs

@endnode


@node "SnapshotWindow" "Snapshot Window"
@next "ScrollWindowDown"
@prev "ScrollWindowBottom"
@{b}SnapshotWindow@{ub}

The SnapshotWindow command is used to save the current position and size of
the current window.

Format:
